  "day": 13,
  "key": "day_13_abraham_believes_promise",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-15",
  "title": {
    "en": "Abraham Trusts God’s Promise"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "God has promised Abraham a future, but time passes and he still has no child.",
      "In this moment, Abraham speaks honestly to God—and God answers with reassurance and a promise."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "reassurance",
        "icon": "shield",
        "label": { "en": "Do Not Be Afraid" },
        "lines": [
          "After this, the word of the Lord came to Abram in a vision:",
          "“Do not be afraid, Abram.",
          "I am your shield,",
          "your very great reward.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "honesty",
        "icon": "chat",
        "label": { "en": "An Honest Question" },
        "lines": [
          "But Abram said,",
          "“O Sovereign Lord,",
          "what can you give me",
          "since I remain childless,",
          "and the one who will inherit my estate",
          "is Eliezer of Damascus?”",
          "And Abram said,",
          "“You have given me no children;",
          "so a servant in my household will be my heir.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "promise",
        "icon": "family",
        "label": { "en": "A Son from Your Own Body" },
        "lines": [
          "Then the word of the Lord came to him:",
          "“This man will not be your heir,",
          "but a son coming from your own body",
          "will be your heir.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "stars",
        "icon": "stars",
        "label": { "en": "A Picture of the Promise" },
        "lines": [
          "He took him outside and said,",
          "“Look up at the heavens",
          "and count the stars—",
          "if indeed you can count them.”",
          "Then he said to him,",
          "“So shall your offspring be.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "righteousness",
        "icon": "verified",
        "label": { "en": "Belief Counted as Righteousness" },
        "lines": [
          "Abram believed the Lord,",
          "and he credited it to him",
          "as righteousness."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about Abraham’s honesty, God’s reassurance, and how belief is connected with righteousness in this passage?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Genesis 15:1–6"]
  }
}
